<TEXT>
<P>
Gary Payton scored 24 points Thursday night as No. 18 Oregon State got its 
eighth consecutive victory and took over the Pacific 10 Conference lead by 
defeating Washington State, 79-64, at Corvallis, Ore. 
</P>
<P>
Payton played only 11 minutes in the first half because of foul trouble but 
scored 16 points in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
He had four steals to lead the Beavers (13-2 overall, 6-0 in conference play). 
Washington State (7-10, 1-6) was led by Juan Thomas' 14 points. 
</P>
<P>
Oregon State led from the start until Washington State tied the score, 43-43, 
with 16 minutes left on Jason Thompson's tip-in. Oregon State regained control, 
taking a 60-50 lead on Karl Anderson's basket with 10:11 left. 
</P>
<P>
The Beavers, who shot 85% from the foul line in the second half, made 10 of 12 
free throws in the final 10 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
Oregon 65, Washington 54 -- Terrell Brandon made two three-point shots late in 
the game to lead the Ducks at Eugene, Ore. 
</P>
<P>
