<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARCACCINI TO COMPLETE SUSPENSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SAM FARMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
G. C. Marcaccini, the second-leading scorer for Notre Dame High, has decided to 
complete a one-month suspension from the basketball team and remain enrolled at 
the school. 
</P>
<P>
Marcaccini said that he was suspended after he tampered with a fire 
extinguisher, setting off a smoke alarm in the Palo Alto hotel in which the 
team was staying during a December holiday tournament. 
</P>
<P>
An entire floor of the hotel was evacuated. 
</P>
<P>
Marcaccini, a junior who is averaging 18 points a game, said that he will 
resume practicing with the team Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame Coach Mick Cady was unavailable for comment. 
</P>
<P>
Transferring to Taft was an option Marcaccini said he had seriously considered. 
</P>
<P>
"That would have been if things were really bad," he said. "I was pretty close. 
. . . I talked to the junior varsity coach and he said I fit in. I'm a decent 
athlete and I like to run and gun." 
</P>
<P>
Marcaccini said that he has resolved his differences with Cady. 
</P>
<P>
"I really like him a lot and he really likes me," Marcaccini said. "He's a 
free-spirited guy." SAM FARMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
