<P>
VOLUNTEERS NEEDED TO CLEAN WETLANDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Volunteers are sought to work Saturday on "a major clean-out" of the Outer 
Bolsa Bay in the Bolsa Chica Ecological Reserve. 
</P>
<P>
Lorraine Faber, a board member of Amigos de Bolsa Chica, said that volunteers 
should report to the ecological reserve's parking lot on Warner Avenue, near 
Pacific Coast Highway, at 8 a.m. Saturday. The cleanup will be from 8 a.m. 
until noon, she said. 
</P>
<P>
"This is an opportunity to see the mud flats up close and personal, so wear old 
clothes and shoes," Faber said. "Gloves will be necessary and wading boots 
desirable." 
</P>
<P>
The volunteers will remove debris, such as boards and tires, that have been 
thrown into the marsh. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, call (714) 897-7003. 
