<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
$2.3 MILLION TO GO TO KATELLA AVENUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Katella Avenue will receive $2.3 million worth of improvements this year, 
including a traffic signal coordination project, new storm drains and the 
widening of a busy intersection. 
</P>
<P>
The city has received a $1.6-million grant to coordinate traffic signals on 
Katella Avenue from the San Gabriel River Freeway to the Orange Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
The grant was made by the Orange County Transportation Commission, which is 
funding projects to improve traffic on regionally significant streets such as 
Katella. 
</P>
<P>
A $368,000 storm drain also will be installed on Katella from State College 
Boulevard to Lewis Street as part of a Board of Supervisors plan to improve 
arterial roads. And the county will be paying for a widening of the 
intersection of Katella and State College to improve traffic. The widening will 
cost $366,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
