<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
American Shuffles U.S.-Europe Routes: American Airlines said it will open five 
new routes to Europe, adding 26 flights a week. 
</P>
<P>
The Dallas-based carrier said the routes, which will start this summer, are 
between Chicago and London, Glasgow, Scotland, Munich and Dusseldorf, West 
Germany, and between Miami to London. Citing a shortage of long-haul aircraft, 
the airline also said it will drop or postpone the start of flights on a number 
of European routes, including between Chicago and Helsinki, Finland, and 
Warsaw, and Dallas to Barcelona, Spain. It will also drop nonstop service 
between New York and Frankfurt, West Germany. 
</P>
</TEXT>
