</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOCUS: MOLA CENTRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mola Centre, located on 40 acres in Irvine, is a mixed-use project that is 
designed as an urban village and features classic European styling. Grading has 
begun on the project, and five sculptures of white Carrera marble, created by 
artist Paolo Borghi of Italy, were unveiled as the centerpiece of the project 
last month. 
</P>
<P>
Phase I of the center is planned to include an office tower, a 164-unit 
residential condominium tower, other condominiums and apartment units, a 
2,100-seat theater complex, a health club, a nightclub and a day-care center, 
as well as retail and restaurant space. Phase II will add a 450-room hotel. 
</P>
<P>
FACTS AND FIGURES 
</P>
<P>
Address: Jamboree Boulevard and Campus Drive, Irvine 
</P>
<P>
Developer: Mola Development Corp., Newport Beach 
</P>
<P>
Architect: McLarand, Vasquez &amp; Partners Inc., Costa Mesa 
</P>
<P>
Square feet: 486,000 in the office tower 
</P>
<P>
Source: Mola Development Corp. 
</P>
</TEXT>
