<HEADLINE>
<P>
BESTSELLERS ON CASSETTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Clipboard researched by Susan Davis Greene / Los Angeles Times; Graphics by 
Doris Shields / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For those of us whose spare time is at a premium, or who are just lazy, but 
still want to to be "well read," books on tape are the fashion and convenience 
of the moment. Here's a list of the hottest "electronic books" from 10 spots 
around the county: 
