THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
U.S. SOCCER TEAM PREPS FOR CUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The U.S. soccer team said today that it would play Bermuda, Hungary, Finland 
and either East Germany or Poland as part of its preparation for the World Cup. 
</P>
<P>
Sunil Gulati, chairman of the international games committee of the U.S. Soccer 
Federation, said the U.S. team would play at Bermuda on Feb. 16 and would play 
Finland on March 10 at Tampa, Fla. The other games will be played later in 
March. 
</P>
