<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA ANITA; 
</P>
<P>
LIVE A DREAM, WRETHAM TO LEAD SAN MARCOS FIELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A field of 14 headed by Live the Dream and Wretham was entered today in 
Sunday's $150,000-added San Marcos Handicap at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
Live the Dream, winner of the Hollywood Derby, and Wretham, winner of the San 
Gabriel Handicap, were assigned 119 pounds each for the 38th running of the 1 
1/4-mile race for 4-year-olds and up on Santa Anita's turf course. 
</P>
<P>
Live the Dream will be ridden by Chris McCarron and Wretham will be ridden by 
Laffit Pincay. 
</P>
<P>
Others entered were Fair Judgment, who will be ridden by Martin Pedroza and was 
assigned 118 pounds; Prince Ruffian, Fernando Toro, 115; Colway Rally, Jorge 
Velasquez, 115; Putting, Corey Black, 114; Samoan, Jerry Bailey, 114; River 
Warden, Russell Baze, 114; King Mab, Thierry Jarnet, 113; Impossible Stream, 
Sandy Hawley, 113; Two Moccasins, Gary Boulanger, 112; Timefighter, Rafael 
Meza, 112; Master Treaty, Lanfranco Dettori, 111, and Capel Meister, Goncalino 
Almeida, 110. 
</P>
<P>
If all 14 entries go to the post, the total purse will be $174,600 and the 
winner will collect $107,100. 
</P>
<P>
A field of seven headed by Stormy But Valid has been entered in Saturday's 
$100,000-added Santa Monica Handicap at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
Stormy But Valid will be ridden by Gary Stevens and was assigned high weight of 
119 pounds for the 33rd running of the seven-furlong race for older fillies and 
mares. 
</P>
<P>
Others entered were Survive, who will be ridden by Baze and was assigned 118 
pounds; Hot Novel, Almeida, 117; Stocks Up, Pincay, 117; Baba Cool, Black, 117; 
Hidden Garden, McCarron, 115, and Solid Eight, Alex Solis, 114. 
</P>
